column5: Well its getting closer 3 more sleepies and im in temagami...sled is gassed up, tackle is in check, sleeping bag and clothes are ready...truck inspected by shop...all i need now is to catch some fish...CANT WAIT...p.s yes beverages ready...any advice at this point would be great..thanks
wish I could help, but I have yet to catch a fish there but in 10 days I will be trying again good luck
C'mon Terry you can do it...make sure wayne takes you to the honey hole...
Advise... take your high rubber boots !  And what Terry... you're going fishing toooo..
wayne..thanks i will do that...ive been watching the weather..supposed to be +9 on wed but then -10-15 for the rest of the week...do you think she'll freeze up ok for friday morning...

I sure hope so Rob. Hope it's enough of a melt down to let it freeze solid. When exactly are you leaving and I'll try to get an update for you before you go... maybe john the fisherman will post as well with a Bear Island view of things.
wayne ..im leaving 2:00 am friday morning..should be fishing by 9:00am friday morning...
Okay.. well leave some for us for the following week! lol
hey dont jinx me...lol... make sure terry catches this time...give it up wayne, share those spots....
Be sure to take your OFC Community.com logo and a camera for the tourney!!!  Get us a nice one!!!
i will gcd...i'll try and get a good one
hey walleye master ,new to this site ,but been fishing temagami for years .going up the last week in feb. ,can't wait ,let me know how u did

hey deepwater...welcome aboard...i usually fish the last week of Feb as well...had to move trip up a week this year because im starting a huge job, when i get back...will try my best to catch a big one

Hey Walleyemaster...I know how you feel    I can't wait to get up there....hopefully we'll see you out on the hub on Sunday morning    Just follow the tracks from the red Patriot to the hole with all the fish...I hope

Hi guys, i just posted my intro earlier  , but wanted to say hello  as I am headin up next wednesday to Temagami ...made my fishfinder mods, and sled to haul my gear.... can't wait... looks like the temps will drop back down by the weekend good luck
two more sleepies....
Yah... just don't make it three on the way up at 2am !
lol...thanks wayne..

Well,  The snow on the lake has gone down at least a 1/2 foot.  The ice road was a little soft on top today, with some small skims of water on top.  TFN has been plowing with the 5 ton now, and today would be a good day to plow before all those little tire ridges freeze by the weekend.  I have not been on the sled in a few days, but I will say that the snow was getting almost a bit too deep before this melt.  700's can be a bit hard on gas when driving around breaking trail.  Not tough going with a good sled. Just MPG. There is slush to be found, but it is not very deep.  I was on a lake just past that I was on a few years ago with slush over the knee.  There was none the other day.  Once it turns -17 for Fri. night that will stiffin it all up on top for sure.  It should be perfect for heading into some unbroken back lakes for specks or pike.  JTF
Great info John....hopefully it will all come together by the weekend....4 more sleeps for me....*sigh*
all right...good news i think...1 more sleepie before the swim....

My buddy made accomodations for us at Lance Whites place (  I think )  was just wondering what the ice depth was like on the ice road as to whether I would take the truck and enclosed trailer out on the ice.  Read a little further up they were plowing with the five ton.  I have a dodge diesel and a 27 foot enclosed trailer you input would put my mind at ease.

hey we are heading up to that area  next weekend not quite temagami but  Tilden lake  just wondering should i bring the sled or  the 4 wheeler  ???  is there still snow up there its nice and green here
